Setting Up Nextcloud on docker behind nginx
===========================================
In nginx config (to set domain cloud.janskowronski.com to 9999)

server {
        listen 80;
        listen [::]:80;
        server_name cloud.janskowronski.com;
        location / {
                proxy_pass http://localhost:9999;

        }
        index index.html;
        client_max_body_size 1024M;

}

Persistant data will be here:
mkdir /srv/nextcloud

docker run -d -v /srv/nextcloud:/var/www/html -p 9999:80 nextcloud

Then do the initial setup by going to cloud.janskowronski.com and creating admin

Default the host will be set to localhost:9999 and some links will not work, so edit config file /srv/nextcloud/config/config.php, by adding:

'overwritehost'=>'cloud.janskowronski.com',

and it should work!

